common.name: slender wheat grass
Comments: identified by Derek Johnson - Sample collected in Stand 8 in 2005 was initially called Ag-inexpa. Was called AGSU - Agropyron subsecundum - in stands 1 and 2 before 2005 based on Moss 1st edition (verified by George LaRoi)

common.name: silvery-flowered sedge
Comments: identified by Derek Johnson - called "CX-NRLF" in Stands 3 and 4 or "CX-NWLF" in Stands 6 and 8 on 2005 fieldsheet

Derek was unable to give a confirmed identification for this carex species in 2005 - "CX-BYEL" = "Carex Big Yellow" was very abundant and collected in Stand 4 in 2005 - its average cover was ca. 10% (verified by George LaRoi)
